trans-unit.source: This nodes implements all the physics logic needed to simulate a car. It is based on the raycast vehicle system commonly found in physics engines. You should also add a MeshInstance to this node for the 3D model of your car but this model should not include meshes for the wheels. You should control the vehicle by using the brake, engine_force, and steering properties and not change the position or orientation of this node directly.
